This paper is about Bayesian neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and fall under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic processes and Gaussian processes, which are relevant to "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.SY" (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks for image processing, which falls under "cs.CV" (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed method, which is relevant to "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
